{5...} Nbd7 {Here, Black had 2 major continuations: 5...a6 and the more
aggressive 5...Nbd7 by which Black wants to play the well-known Meran System.
The fundamental idea of this system is that Black wants to develop his
light-square bishop on b7 after the sequence 6.Bd3 dxc4 7.Bxc4 b5 8.Bd3 a6.  5.
