which Black wins a tempo by 6...d5xc4. Also, the knight on d7 is ideally
placed as it sustains 2 typical pawn thrust in the center: e6-e5 and c6-c5. At
his 6th move, White can accept Meran playing 6.Bd3 or has some anti-Meran
systems, the most important being 6.Qc2 which is analyzed in this lesson.} 6.
